because we can explictly provide positional information, thus providing 
a computational short-cut. Computer models are also not limited to 
limites of physical space, e.g. my NN model has a 1D positioning system 
but the number of connections is limitless and any neuron can connect to 
any other regardless of positioning. Capitalizing on freedoms we have 
(within computer models) hopefully goes some way to making up for the 
lack of resources available in a computer model when compared to nature.


